wledge of Hall and his practice has had to rely only on a partial, seventeenth-century edition (produced by James Cooke in 1657 and 1679, and re-printed with annotation by Joan Lane as recently as 1996). Cooke’s edition significantly misrepresents Hall by abridging his manuscript (Cooke removed Hall’s conversations with his patients), by errors of translation, and by combining Hall’s work with examples from Cooke’s own medical practice.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aMedicinevEarly works to 1800. 0aMedicinexHistoryy17th century. 0aMedicinezEnglandzStratford-upon-AvonvCase studies. 0aMedicinezEnglandzStratford-upon-AvonxHistoryy17th century. 0aPhysicians (General practice)zEnglandzStratford-upon-Avon. 0aPhysicians. 4aShakespeare 2020. 7aDRAMA / Shakespeare.2bisacsh  aJohn Hall.  aShakespeare.  aStratford-upon-Avon.  acurespatients.  aearly-modern libraries.  aherbalism.  ahistory of medicine.  amedical.  amedicine.1 aEdmondson, Paul, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aWells, Greg, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 2020 eBook-Packagez978311128248040uhttps://doi.org/10.7765/978152613452340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781526134523423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781526134523/original  a978-3-11-128248-0  Manchester University Press 2020 eBook-Packageb2020  aGBV-deGruyter-alles